originalText.text: Wouldn't recommend. She was always late to our sessions and cut it from my time. You will hear the question "why?" about 100 times per session because to be honest, I don't think she's paying attention. I didn't want to write a review and was just going to stop seeing her, but then she scheduled a meeting without my consent in which she still charged me $150 for "canceling". When I told her I would rather just have one last session than paying that much for something I didn't confirm, she waited hours to email back (Mind you, I emailed her my responses in SECONDS) to let me know she filled my spot. She's extremely hard to get in contact with and tbh after most sessions I felt like I needed a therapist just to talk about my therapist. I would say just make sure she's the RIGHT therapist for you and weigh your options. I've never had a therapist as deceitful and spiteful as her. Just be careful. Stay blessed, regardless.
